article.headline: Furman 92, Lipscomb 56
article.story: GREENVILLE, S.C. (AP) -- Freshmen Quan Prowell and Robby Bostain led a potent 3-point attack that carried Furman to a 92-56 win over Lipscomb in the championship of the Jack in the Box Holiday Classic on Tuesday night. Prowell scored a game-high 18 points and hit four of six 3-point shots. Bostain added 17 and sank three of four bonus attempts as the Paladins (7-4) tied a 9-year-old team record with 13 3-point baskets. Freshman guard Brian Fisk scored 16 to pace the Bisons (2-7), who made just four of 23 bonus shots. Prowell made all of his 3-pointers while scoring 16 points in the first half. Furman built a quick 20-7 lead and stretched the margin to 20 at halftime (46-26). Bostain hit a pair of threes early in the second half. The Paladins went up by 25 at 61:36. Ben Earl also hit three bonus shots as Furman finished 13 of 23 from beyond the arc. The Paladins previously hit 13 3-pointers in 1994 against Marshall. Prowell was named Classic MVP, while Bostain and teammate Nick Sanders were elected to the all-tournament team along with Fisk, Nathan Ball of Charleston Southern, and Diondre Larmond of Bethune-Cookman.
